> "Who has limitless accessof those data?" asked Perceptor

LORD ELDER tilted his head as he looked at PERCPETOR. "Limitless?" He
said in a somewhat confused tone. "Anyone directly on board the
Satelite itself." He said carefully. "Anyone with the proper security
clearances."

There was a nod from LEGACY. "If we exclude Cheetor from consideration
then it would be the insect like aliens that would be the most likely
author of these events as they were housed within Cryonosis."

ELDER nodded and said. "Now that I can understand. But how would they
have gotten Cheetor's password?"

"Unknown." LEGACY said. "These are only suppositions that cannot be at
this moment confirmed. However I can at this point see no motive for
the insect aliens to need the satellite." LEGACY's optic flickered,
"There are facts that are still not in evidence."

ELDER nodded again.

LEGACY looked at the screen which showed NIGHTSHIFT hard at work,
"Perhaps if we can send a modulated pulse to the satellite it might
reset it. That is if there is no one on board actively resisting our
efforts."

(TAG)

- Preston
